entries.text: I'm sure all the detours taken...
I just woke up, so my voice isn't coming out at all.
If anything, it's cold, so I sound a bit nasal.
Usually, I take a bath before streaming,
but today I seriously just woke up,
so I haven't taken a bath yet.
I don't have clothes, but Kusa-kun...
took a bath yesterday, you know.
It's just that his next bath
I might be a bit smellier than usual.
Because usually I stream right after getting out.
So I might be a little smellier than usual.
Last time, we had our first sacrificed Pokemon.
And it was taken down by a level 8 Skitty, of all things.
Even though he was our HM user...
So, as a replacement HM user,
Uchu the Lombre has joined the team.
Uchu can't become a Ludicolo without a Water Stone,
so I'm hoping to get one soon.
Also, as shown in the bottom left,
the next gym is the Lavaridge Gym,
so I want to climb this mountain
Man, I really don't want any more sacrifices.
I should copy the house just in case.
I don't think it'll happen, but just in case
I'll put it off to the side for now.
Lavaridge is where the hot springs are, right?
I have a feeling it is.
Oh, there's a Strength boulder here too.
But if I have a Fire-type...
it'll be effective against Grass, Ice, Bug, and Steel?
I really don't have a Pokemon that works well against them.
Don't just keep using that move.
Is this going to poison me?
Yeah, let's whittle it down a bit more.
I thought Donmel was the pre-evolution of Torkoal.
It fights using energy from burning coal.
While blowing smoke from its nostrils,
So it makes a sound similar to its shape.
Um, if I swap Torkoal with Sekiban...
Is that... will I be a bit undermanned?
Yeah, Psychic vs Psychic might be a bit annoying.
But I don't see Psychic types having high defense...
I'd rather be effective against Steel types.
I guess Sekiban is leaving the team for a bit.
Steel types are pretty rock-hard, after all.
I keep hitting this person in the back of the head with my bike.
Wheelies are seriously hard to do.
Maybe I should raise Shupopo with the Exp. Share for now.
Let's heal up just in case.
"Torkoal takes 4x from Water and Ground, so be careful."
"Be a little careful here," that kind of thing.
I thought yesterday I should stream while looking at it.
Found it, found it, found it.
The Onigiriya put this together for me.
This is super easy to understand.
I'll keep this on the side while I play.
replace the character image with Torkoal.
I completely forgot I just gave it to her.
Even though I just did it.
But lately there are a lot of days where I'm sleepy.
Maybe I'm just blaming the cold.
I'm sleepy every day, aren't I?
It's just "kinda sleepy" all the time.
Torkoal-chan is a "hard to make transparent" Pokemon.
Do your best to be transparent.
For those wondering what Okayu is doing right now,
I am currently performing transparency operations on Torkoal.
And I'll erase this one here...
I do this swap work when someone dies,
so messing with this area makes my heart race.
Torkoal looks huge, but I wonder about the actual size.
I have an impression of it being big.
Because the pixel art has so much impact, Torkoal...
Makes me think it must be huge.
"It was small in the Pokemon anime."
So it's actually about that size.
"It looks big because of the smoke."
Koffing really gives that Team Rocket image.
Do I need to clear it to use it?
so your level ends up being totally fine without fighting wild Pokemon.
I want to fight with members other than Shamoji, level-wise.
Wait, I can do a double battle there.
I feel like the person above might use bird Pokemon.
Let's go with this. Hera and Kizoku.
I'm entering at a good time!
I'll show you the fiery Pokemon I caught in the Fiery Path!
"Oh, what a lovely trainer. A romantic battle, please."
"Seeking too much sweetness from an Aroma Lady..."
"makes the sweetness look sweet... The end."
Aroma Ladies are kinda erotic, aren't they?
This party is fine to fight with.
Confusion and Wing Attack to take down Shroomish first.
Makes you ask, "What did Numel do?"
"Himmel would have done that" makes sense somehow.
Ah, if it was Hero Himmel,
he would have made that choice.
"What did Numel do?" is what happens.
Don't leave it to our imagination.
"Let me see how far you've trained your Pokemon!"
I often look at stream impressions.
There was a listener there who really loves Electrike.
they were really looking forward to
an Electrike jumping out of the wild grass.
It made me feel all warm and fuzzy.
Like, "I've been waiting for this moment!"
Ah, well, let's take it out with Shock Wave.
I feel like there's always one fan like that.
You can buy plushies of any Pokemon there.
Paralysis making you unable to move sucks.
Hera is paralyzed and struggling, so maybe I'll ask Kizoku.
"Your training method is a good reference."
"Fight me again if you feel like it."
But there's no way to rematch trainers from the PokeNav, right?
I don't see a Pokemon Center yet, so let's heal him up.
Tawashi, who used to bring me Potions, is no longer here.
Tawashi, who brought me Paralyze Heals, is gone.
But thanks to you, I have plenty of Escape Ropes and Potions.
"I was thinking of using a Pokemon move to make my own room here."
"Try using Secret Power on a tree that looks like it's dropping vines."
"The vines will fall and you can climb up."
"And up there, there's a wide room."
"I'm going to put wonderful things there."
"Oh right, trees aren't the only place to make Secret Bases."
"Try using Secret Power on walls with small indents too."
"I'll go look for other places too. See ya."
Eh, but if possible, I want to make one near a station (Pokemon Center).
No choice, I feel like I have to make someone learn Cut.
Eh, if Uchu becomes a Ludicolo, will he learn Cut?
Do I have to make Owan learn it?
If Ludicolo could learn Cut, I'd be super happy.
If I keep hitting 'A', this will go on forever.
"Today, I'm going to discover new talent here."
"The trainer I focused on today is Okayu-san!"
"Now, the fastest way to see a trainer's skill is to battle!"
"So, I tried battling, but I was completely beaten up."
"If I may give my impressions of the battle..."
"The combo of Marshtomp and Breloom was the best!"
"The Mach Punch used at the end of our match..."
"Was a Mach Punch of friendship between Marshtomp and Breloom!"
"After the match, when I asked Okayu-san..."
"Well then, see you in the next broadcast!"
Maybe I should stay one more night.
Seriously, I don't want to be on TV.
Ah, couldn't I climb this with the Mach Bike?
"I watered them a lot and tons of flowers bloomed!"
"Do your best to grow lots of different colored berries!"
It's true, tons of Razz Berries.
I wonder what Razz Berries taste like.
"Oh my, your Pokemon look quite strong."
I have Shock Wave, you know. Shock Wave.
Step right up, take a look.
I like how they play on words.
"Did I look like I liked them?"
I don't need Smog, do I?
Don't really need Curse either, right?
It's Fire, so it's special, right?
I feel like I don't need it.
Nice, Hera can proceed with battles
I sound nasal today, you see.
Eh, I want to rest at Grandma's again.
Where that reporter was earlier was also Route 111, right?
If I get the bag, walking here...
allows me to collect ash, right?
I have such a memory. Hiyah!
Yeah, we can collect volcanic ash.
We can make flutes, I think.
It feels pretty good when the grass changes color where you run.
Walking on grass covered in volcanic ash...
It's fun because you can see where you walked.
"Do you know why it's relatively cool around here?"
I thought Paras was pure white...
Before, when I played Pokemon Pinball, I didn't know it had those shiitake eyes.
Eh, looks like I'll battle 3 people.
"Thank you, but battle is a separate matter."
Will I fight the person below later?
Too much quirkiness, too much info.
I want to fight it, this Aron.
Maybe switching to Kizoku is better?
Is it because it's part Rock?
Just brute force it, brute force.
I had an image that Electric...
"Are you happy? Are you happy beating someone like me?"
Were you in the middle of collecting volcanic ash?
Why were you three together here?
I was curious about that, extremely.
Baltoy is Ground, right? Probably Rock too.
Stop showing Zigzagoon in the top right.
It was a tragic event, you know.
Especially since I was just about...
thinking of evolving Zigzagoon into Linoone.
Lost to a Skitty around here.
Eh, mister, you were hiding a Nugget?
Let's go back to Grandma's to heal.
There was a lumpy spot behind the mister...
and a Golden Ball (Nugget) came out of it.
I don't want to forget that playful spirit.
I don't know if it's 200 but...
There are several types of patterns, I think.
That surprise really made my throat rasp just now.
If Owan can go, I want him to join.
Looks cute, like it has bangs.
Looks like a "Hachiware" (mask pattern) cat, cute.
To think this is 1 in 4 billion is amazing.
I'll never meet it again. Never.
Is it hard to put them in other series?
It's been a long time since I saw Spinda.
We don't see them at all in recent Pokemon games.
Well, I guess that makes sense.
So that exists, thanks to random...
"It's fun to blow glass flutes in time with the boss's talking."
"It's covered in volcanic ash, peko peko."
"Walk through piles of ash and it turns black from collecting soot."
"If you think you've collected enough ash, come to me, peko."
So Pekoland was here all along, in the Hoenn region.
I would have brought a souvenir or something.
There are tons of kids playing Ninja here.
The chain is getting a bit long (far from PC).
I feel like I still have Antidotes.
Body Slam looks like it'll work.
I don't think I need Smokescreen.
If you ask, I'll exchange PokeNavs.
You used to sell them to me.
Even now, I'm saved by the items Tawashi picked up.
"They can turn this volcanic ash into glass!"
"This ash is proof the earth is alive."
The party is solidifying pretty well.
Let's go with Owan and Shupopo.
"Be my opponent to wake me up!"
"I'll blow you away with these wings!"
Oh, might be my first time fighting a Bird Keeper.
I gotta withdraw Kizoku, that's bad.
Actually, Kizoku might be fine fighting as is.
Hera is weak to Flying, so that's bad.
Before evolving, he fought evenly with a Skarmory.
Since he was a Taillow, he's been chasing Skarmory's back.
Their Swellow is focusing energy too.
Getting to the town was super far, by the way.
I remember loving the music here.
"That means you're using the Storage System I made."
"Because you spoke to me while I was in front of a PC, you must want to use it."
"I'm super happy to meet a trainer using my Storage System."
"If you like, please come visit my house."
"I wonder what Pokemon looked like in ancient times."
"Maybe the Fossil Maniac on the edge of town can tell you."
"I plant sturdy trees that can grow even in volcanic ash."
"A suspicious person came out of Professor Cozmo's house."
Ah, this is where you need Tiny Mushrooms, right?
"I know all the moves Pokemon learn as they grow..."
"And I can teach them to Pokemon."
Ah, Heart Scale! Nostalgic. I don't have any.
"Have you battled Flannery, the Gym Leader of Lavaridge Town?"
Is there a Takane Lui here?
"Have you battled Flannery, the Gym Leader of Lavaridge Town?"
"Apparently he was one of the Elite Four at the Pokemon League."
"I'm sure Flannery will become a wonderful trainer too."
"Professor Cozmo went to Meteor Falls on Route 114 with people from Team Magma."
Ah, isn't that where you get Lunatone and Solrock?
"My big brother is the Fossil Maniac! He's a fossil-loving nice guy."
"By the way, he also loves digging holes, so he dug this one himself."
"Here, take this so you can dig holes like my brother."
He's definitely digging way outside his property lines without permission.
There's no way his land extends this far.
Or maybe he built a tiny house on a huge plot of land.
"Fossil Maniac, fossil-loving nice guy... Do you want a fossil too?"
"The fossils found here are all mine, so I won't give you any."
"If you really want one, go search the desert where there's lots of rock and sand."
I want to raise Owan's level a bit, is that okay?
Barboach doesn't have Ground type yet, right?
I haven't called Akihiko lately, and he hasn't called me.
I have a fishing buddy named Akihiko.
I don't know where he is.
There he is, there he is.
"Next time I battle Okayu, I definitely won't lose."
Ah, but they use Water types.
Emerald has a lot of doubles.
Maybe I should target the right one first.
I'll ask Kizoku to handle it.
When Nuzleaf appears, it's a bit troublesome.
"My Pokemon just keeps increasing and everyone runs away..."
So Roar is the move machine.
Ah, feeding it makes them hate you.
Owan was super strong even as a Shroomish though.
I don't want to increase the graves any more.
One more with Owan as is.
The low PP is the only difficult part.
I wonder if he can become a Ludicolo.
Ludicolo really left an impression on me.
Do you know the Ludicolo from Pokemon Colosseum?
"I love changing the layout, so I'm collecting berries."
Look at the number of PCs.
"When I get absorbed in research, it ends up like this."
"It's embarrassing so please keep it a secret."
"Advice from me, the creator of the Storage System:"
"You should organize properly so you know..."
It's not an item, it's a Monster Ball.
This shape of PC is nostalgic.
When I was in elementary school, maybe?
Like 4th grade, these PCs were in the computer lab.
I didn't have a PC at home.
I want to let Shupopo fight soon.
The levels are lining up nicely.
I want to take down Graveler quickly.
I don't imagine a trainer's Pokemon using Self-Destruct...
Do some know it from the start?
"The fun of camping is fishing, fireworks, and ghost stories."
I thought the fun of camping was the food.
Some of you might have noticed...
I remember up to Sandshrew, Parasect.
After that, honestly, I'm not sure.
Yeah, I only half-remember, but I say it with confidence.
"Eh? Eh? Abra? Eh? What was it? What was it?"
will think, "Ah yeah, I think that was it."
So I try to say it decisively.
They'll teach me in the comments.
Yeah, I'm forcing my way through.
Lately I display the lyrics at the bottom so
it's obvious if I make a mistake.
But some people enjoy the stream without looking at the screen,
so I figure those people won't notice.
Amazing. I see that intro a lot.
"If you think the world is full of meaningful things..."
Want to take a step, Shupo?
I seriously wouldn't be able to stand back up.
There was a reason for that just now.
I thought I had to change the length (of the layout).
I tried to withdraw Slugma, right?
Ah, was it fighting a Grass type?
Ah no, no. I was fighting a Fire type and wanted to withdraw the Grass type, but sent it out.
"Just kinda watching for the first time." Welcome.
Even though you just stopped by casually,
it might turn into a long relationship.
"but I kinda ended up watching for a long time,"
"and started watching the next stream too."
Encounters like that are nice too.
Man, I'm curious what kind of call Buhiko will make.
"Those who neglect preparation shall not climb the mountain."
"How much have you evolved your Pokemon?"
Everyone except Torkoal has experienced evolution.
I'm running out of Mega Drain.
Trainers everywhere learn Self-Destruct way too much!
Shock Wave is just too effective, it saves me.
It reminds me of Gold and Silver...
This is tough because the path is long.
It's important not to get lazy.
Because there are so many of them.
I tend to get lazy, you see.
But knowing laziness leads to death...
There are just a lot of trainers.
It's not that big of a deal.
Wow, they put a hex on me.
Mach Punch works on Geodude too, right?
Well, fine. Mach Punch it is.
Hera's getting a lot of screen time lately.
I need to bring out Kizoku bit by bit.
"First time watching this stream, what's the house in the back?"
This is, I'm doing a Life Play challenge (Nuzlocke).
Normally in Pokemon, if they faint, you take them to the Center...
But the rule is if they die once, faint once, they are isolated in the PC box and not used.
But it's easy to see the unusable Pokemon in the top right.
Wow, the graphics are super pretty.
"With this Meteorite, that guy at Mt. Chimney..."
"I don't know who you are, but if you plan to interfere with Team Magma, no mercy!"
"Wait, Team Magma! Thinking you can bend the world to your will is a big mistake!"
"Whatever, we got the Meteorite. Let's go to Mt. Chimney."
"Hyohyo! See ya, stupid Team Aqua Archie!"
"You're... we met at the Museum in Slateport."
"At that time, I thought you were a Team Magma grunt."
"Team Magma claims to expand the land..."
"They are a dangerous group repeating destructive acts."
"They are the archenemies of us, Team Aqua, who love the sea."
"Archie-sama! We have to chase Team Magma!"
"Right. There's no telling what those Magma guys will do at Mt. Chimney."
"Okayu, you should watch out for Team Magma too."
But this is an interesting mechanic.
Team Aqua doesn't look like bad people.
Team Magma doesn't look that bad.
It's an amazing system that makes even kids feel that.
"Team Magma asked me to guide them here..."
"But I was tricked and they took the Meteorite."
"And then a similar bunch called Team Aqua showed up..."
"What does Team Magma plan to do at Mt. Chimney?"
Right, right. Even as a child... different perspectives, different values.
You kinda understand that, which is a great theme.
"If that's the case, I'd be happy."
Delcatty needs a Moon Stone? Right, right.
Back then, among evolved Pokemon, Delcatty...
I feel like it was the weakest.
Is there a Pokemon weaker than Delcatty now?
"This sandy beach is my secret training spot!"
That sounds like a Vocaloid song title.
For a while, Rerulili-san made a series...
Like "Something-Something Girl" series, there were lots.
But I don't think there was "Land Claim Girl."
Yeah, yeah. Like "Brain Fluid Explosion Girl."
"This is my construct rate!" Like that.
Crap, I was laughing and didn't see what she sent out.
Can you just dismiss that as being "hard-headed"?
It's soft. Not hard-headed at all.
Weren't there kids who wanted to bump heads?
If we went *bonk*, it hurt so bad.
But they existed in elementary school.
There was a boom like that.
The people on this land are a bit...
Spoink, who dies if it stops bouncing...
Satoshi held it firmly with both hands.
Spoinks in the anime stop moving normally though.
Wait, isn't Seviper a Normal type?
"Who are you!?" I shouldn't have come down here.
If I go down, I can't get back up without Surf, right?
Right? If I go down, it's the Skitty zone.
I should buy Full Heals later.
If I have Cheri Berries, that works too.
By the way, don't I need to check on the berries?
I can't go to those berries anymore.
I can't go back until I have Fly.
It's a berry incident! Berry incident!
Bagon appears at a low rate.
Those 600-BST types are hard to raise.
Even if it appears, I probably can't raise it.
I might catch it as a memento though.
Three-stage evolutions with slow leveling are tough.
It's the day after Valentine's, so maybe one chance?
Would be nice if it existed.
The circle in the middle is connected like a sausage.
That thing often seen in anime. Back in the day.
The protagonist's rival character is a huge ladies' man.
And just when he says "Hey, I'm not done talking yet!"
With footprint marks all over his face.
"If you expand the land, the place for Water Pokemon to live decreases!"
Both of them, or both organizations, want to make the world better.
Are you okay? That Poochyena in the middle is getting bullied hard. Isn't that too intense?
"Don't interfere! Reviving HIM is for everyone's sake!"
Right, everyone does it for everyone.
"Those Team Aqua jerks, always getting in our way!"
"Look at what the Magma bunch is plotting."
"They're trying to pour the stolen Meteorite's power into the volcano!"
"If they do that, the volcano will erupt!"
Only the last vowel sound matches.
Don't you hate them too much?
You just hate everything about them.
Team Magma will likely use Fire Pokemon.
"We're going to move on top of the magma!"
No, the Team Magma girl is cute.
Team Aqua's outfits look like Onigirians (Okayu's fans), which is nice.
The levels are getting closer, steadily.
Wait, the outfit shape is like Team Magma.
But Onigirians are like Team Aqua.
I don't think you need to build a home on top of magma.
"You should just go float in the sea!"
"Our Leader says it's something that will make everyone happy."
This kind of thing is the hardest to deal with.
"I already gave the Meteorite from Meteor Falls to the Leader!"
"Trying to get land for free, lol."
Or rather, building a house on magma seems structurally worrying.
Is that normal? Is it safe?
There are a lot of Land Claim Girls.
Um, Kizoku is good against Dark types...
Owan is technically good against Dark...
As long as Poochyena doesn't breathe fire.
I have an image of them breathing fire.
If they try hard, won't they breathe it?

Ugh, I want him to learn a stronger Water move than Water Gun.
Probably hard until I get Surf.
I have an image of getting burned.
"A meteorite is fitted into a mysterious device."
"It seems to be storing some kind of energy."
"That energy will work deep within the crater..."
"Archie was grumbling about a child hindering Team Aqua's activities lately."
"Hmph. So you intend to interfere with us, Team Magma, as well?"
"Listen well! Living things came onto land and evolved."
"That is why we, Team Magma, aim for the development of people and Pokemon by expanding the land!"
"For that, we need HIM who sleeps in this mountain!"
"Oops, there was no need for you to know that much."
"More importantly, I shall teach you what happens when you interfere with us!"
I kind of want to ask Kizoku.
Right, our levels have climbed to match theirs.
I feel like Confusion would fix this soon...
"For Maxie to let his guard down..."
No, it was super dangerous for us too.
"Fine. I will give up on this for now."
"But Team Magma's activities do not end here."
"Thanks to you, we prevented Team Magma's destructive activities."
"Well, whatever. We will continue to chase Team Magma."

Meteorite Get. Should I heal up?
I wonder... if I go down immediately...
I think I'll go to the Pokemon Center.
While going to the Pokemon Center,
I think I need more Full Heals.

And go to the Friendly Shop...

I'll buy a few more Super Potions.

Exactly the mountain I was looking for.
Shouldn't I have brought the Acro Bike?
I hope there isn't a Water Stone here.
If there was a Water Stone here, I wouldn't be able to recover.
No, but it's unlikely to be here.

Shall I give that to Uchu?
Shall I give him the Exp. Share soon?
"What I'm doing in a place like this..."

so he might have been in a bad mood.
Because I interfered with that project.

"Don't mind me, just go where you like."

"So it's not suited for a picnic."

Does this mean I'll come back here?

Let's do our best with Owan and Hera.

I don't have much advantage against Shroomish.
